    "eyebrow": "Settlement Patterns",
    "num": "04",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">04</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Patterns</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Where and How Did Texicans Settle?</h2><ul><li>Settled primarily in South and Central Texas regions</li><li>Communities centered around ranching, farming, and missions</li><li>Settlement influenced by Texas geography: rivers, plains, and hills</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican settlements were shaped by Texas's diverse geography, favoring areas suitable for agriculture and ranching. Missions also served as cultural and religious centers. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican ranches along the Rio Grande utilized river access for livestock and irrigation.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Examine how geography influenced Texican economic activities and settlement locations.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not assume Texicans settled uniformly; geography created varied lifestyles.</p></div></div>",
