    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">06</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texicans and the Texas Revolution</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Roles in Early Texas History</h2><ul><li>Texicans participated actively in the Texas Revolution (1835-1836)</li><li>Fought for independence from Mexico alongside Anglo settlers</li><li>Helped shape the Republic of Texas’s early political landscape</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans were key players in the Texas Revolution, contributing to military efforts and political formation of the Republic of Texas. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican leaders signing the Texas Declaration of Independence in 1836.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze the motivations Texicans had for supporting Texas independence.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not assume all Texicans opposed Mexico; loyalties were complex and varied.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide6\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines the term &#39;Texican&#39;?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;A person of mixed Mexican and Texan heritage&quot;,&quot;A European settler in Texas&quot;,&quot;A Native American tribe in Texas&quot;,&quot;A nickname for all Texans&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; specifically refers to people of mixed Mexican and Texan heritage, reflecting the cultural blending in early Texas history.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain the role of Texicans in the Texas Revolution and the formation of the Republic of Texas.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should include key contributions of Texicans to the Texas Revolution, mention of their cultural background, and how they influenced the Republic&#39;s formation.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texicans played a crucial role in the Texas Revolution by fighting for independence from Mexico. Their mixed cultural heritage helped shape the political and social landscape of the new Republic of Texas.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans fought in the Texas Revolution and helped establish the Republic of Texas&quot;,&quot;They contributed culturally and politically to early Texas history&quot;,&quot;Texicans were key figures in the independence movement and republic formation&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
