    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Political Diversity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Political and Social Composition</h2><ul><li>Texicans included landowners, ranchers, and political leaders</li><li>Diverse views on governance and relations with Mexico and the U.S.</li><li>Political diversity influenced Republic of Texas policies</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican society was politically diverse, with varying perspectives that shaped early Texas governance and social structures. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican ranchers advocating for land rights versus urban leaders favoring different policies.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Consider how political diversity within a group affects decision-making and identity.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Avoid assuming Texicans had a single political viewpoint or agenda.</p></div></div>",
