    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Treaty Impact</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Treaty of Guadalupe Hidalgo and Texican Identity</h2><ul><li>Treaty (1848) ended Mexican-American War, redrawing Texas borders</li><li>Affected land ownership and citizenship status of Texicans</li><li>Shifted cultural and political identity in border regions</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The treaty significantly impacted Texicans by altering territorial boundaries and legal statuses, influencing identity and community dynamics. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican families navigating new U.S. laws on land and citizenship after 1848.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how legal treaties can reshape cultural identities and community structures.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Do not overlook the treaty’s social and cultural effects beyond political boundaries.</p></div></div>",
